txt.en: Dunlendings can be found near the ruined ring of Isengard in Nan Curunír.\n\nYou have discovered Dunlendings trapped by rubble in the aftermath of the Battle of Isengard. You should free them and send them on their way.
You have freed many Dunlendings from the ruins of Isengard.

You have freed many Dunlendings from the shattered remains of Isengard and allowed them to return to their people. Your mercy and that of the Ents at the conclusion of the battle shall be remembered in Dunland.

You have encountered a Dunlending trapped under the rubble of the ring of Isengard. Despite your past conflicts with the Dunlendings in Nan Curunír and Rohan, Quickbeam and the Ents spared them at the battle's end and you feel that such a show of mercy might do much to ease the tensions between all involved.\n\nIf you are able to free them from the wreckage, perhaps they can be directed home to Dunland.
Dunlendings trapped under the remains of the ring of Isengard struggle to free themselves and flee from Nan Curunír.
